State MSM Profile: Utah

Background & Methods

In 2015-2016, researchers at Emory University partnered with colleagues at the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) to develop methods to estimate the number of men who have sex with men (MSM) residing in each county in the United States. Using population and housing data from the American Community Survey and estimates from two peer-reviewed publications (Oster et al., 2015 & Purcell et al., 2012), they derived an indirect estimate of MSM population sizes that took into account both the urbanicity of the county as well as its density of households with a male householder and a male same-sex partner.

The full methodology is published in the Journal of Medical Internet Research - Public Health and Surveillance:

Grey JA, Bernstein KT, Sullivan PS, Purcell DW, Chesson HW, Gift TL, Rosenberg ES. Estimating the population sizes of men who have sex with men in US states and counties using data from the American Community Survey. JMIR Public Health Surveill 2016;2(1):e14. DOI: 10.2196/publichealth.5365

Overview of MSM in Utah

An estimated 33,294 men who have sex with men (MSM) resided in Utah in 2013, representing 0.7% of the 4,503,084 MSM in the United States. Of the 962,285 adult men of Utah, 3.5% had had sex with another man in the past 5 years, which was less than the overall percentage of adult men in the United States who were MSM (3.9%).

Most MSM in Utah resided in central counties of large metropolitan areas (69.8%). Including both central and fringe counties, 71.7% resided in a large metropolitan area.


Percentage of MSM by urbanicity, United States and Utah, 2013

MSM in Utah Counties

Among counties or county-equivalent areas in Utah, Salt Lake County had the largest population of MSM at 23,243, representing 69.8% of all MSM in the state. Salt Lake County also had the highest percentage of MSM among adult men in Utah at 6.2%. This was greater than the percentage for Utah as a whole, which was 3.5% of adult men.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.



MSM in Utah Metropolitan Statistical Areas

Salt Lake City Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Salt Lake City MSA had the largest metropolitan population of MSM in Utah at 23,874, or 71.7% of all MSM in the state. Of the 391,137 adult men in Salt Lake City, an estimated 6.1% were MSM.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.




Ogden-Clearfield Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Ogden-Clearfield MSA had a population of 3,505 MSM, or 10.5% of all MSM in Utah. Of the 203,269 adult men in Ogden-Clearfield, an estimated 1.7% were MSM.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.




Provo-Orem Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Provo-Orem MSA had a population of 2,298 MSM, or 6.9% of all MSM in Utah. Of the 173,371 adult men in Provo-Orem, an estimated 1.3% were MSM.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.




St. George Metropolitan Statistical Area

The St. George MSA had a population of 701 MSM, or 2.1% of all MSM in Utah. Of the 48,422 adult men in St. George, an estimated 1.4% were MSM.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.




Logan Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Logan MSA overlaps two states: Idaho and Utah. The Utah portion of the MSA had 605 MSM, or 1.8% of all MSM in the state and 93.1% of the 650 MSM in the MSA. Of 38,609 adult men in the Utah part of Logan, 1.6% were MSM. This was greater than the overall percentage of MSM among adult men in the MSA, which was 1.5% of adult men (650 out of 42,799).

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.
